PRIVACY POLICY FOR TennisPro
Last Updated: January 10, 2026

1. INTRODUCTION
This Privacy Policy describes how TennisPro ("App," "we," "our," or "us"), developed by Veera R Maddiapti, collects, uses, and protects your information. This App is a tournament management platform designed for users in India. By using the App, you consent to the data practices described in this policy in accordance with the Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act, 2023.

Developer Contact: mveera21@gmail.com

2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We only collect data that is necessary for the core functionality of organizing and participating in physical tennis tournaments.

A. Information You Provide Directly (Consent-Based):

User Profile: Name, phone number, age, and villa/community name.

Tournament Data: Tournament names, venues, dates, and match formats.

Photos: If you choose to upload a profile picture or match scorecards, we collect those images.

Access Codes: We use shared codes (Admin/Player/Umpire) for role-based authentication and tournament access.

B. Information Collected Automatically:

Firebase Analytics: We collect non-identifiable usage patterns and feature engagement.

Crashlytics: We collect technical logs to fix bugs and improve app stability.

C. What we DO NOT collect:

No Payments: We do not collect, process, or store any payment information, bank details, or UPI IDs.

No Sensitive Tracking: We do not collect precise GPS location, contacts, or SMS data.

3. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION
App Functionality: To place you in the correct age-group bracket (e.g., U-18 or Seniors) and display your name on match schedules and tournament brackets.

Communication: To facilitate tournament updates or coordinate match timings via the phone number provided.

Security: To verify participants and prevent duplicate registrations using Villa/Community details.

4. DATA STORAGE & SHARING
Storage: Your data is stored securely in Firebase Cloud Firestore (Google Cloud).

Sharing: Your Name and Match Scores are visible to other participants within the same tournament. Your contact details and villa information are shared only with the specific Tournament Organizer for event coordination and residency verification.

Third-Party Services: We use Google Firebase for backend services. You can view Google’s privacy terms at policies.google.com/privacy.

5. YOUR RIGHTS (DPDP ACT 2023 COMPLIANCE)
Under Indian law, you have the following rights:

Right to Access: You can view your profile and registration data within the App.

Right to Correction: You can request updates to inaccurate info.

Right to Withdrawal: You may withdraw your consent for data collection at any time. (Note: This will result in removal from the tournament).

Right to Erasure: You can request the permanent deletion of your data and photos by emailing mveera21@gmail.com. We will process erasure requests within 30 days.

6. CHILDREN’S PRIVACY
While the App is used for tennis tournaments that may include minors, registration must be performed by a parent or legal guardian for anyone under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect data from children without parental consent through the registration process.

7. DATA SECURITY
We implement industry-standard security measures, including:

SSL/TLS Encryption for all data in transit.

Firestore Security Rules to prevent unauthorized database access.

App Check to ensure only our official app can communicate with the server.

